# Jira API Proxy Test Endpoints
# Note: All endpoints except health checks now require Authorization header

### Health Check (No auth required)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/
Accept: application/json

### Proxy Health Check (No auth required)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/rest/api/2/health
Accept: application/json

### Get Server Info (Required for JetBrains IDE) - API v2
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/rest/api/2/serverInfo
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Basic {{base64-encoded-username:token}}

### Get Server Info (Required for JetBrains IDE) - API latest
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/rest/api/latest/serverInfo
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Basic {{base64-encoded-username:token}}

### Search Issues with JQL - API v2
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/rest/api/2/search?jql=project=TEST&maxResults=10
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Basic {{base64-encoded-username:token}}

### Search Issues with JQL - API latest (JetBrains)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/rest/api/latest/search?jql=assignee=currentUser()&maxResults=10
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Basic {{base64-encoded-username:token}}

### Search Issues with JQL - JetBrains specific endpoint
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/rest/api/latest/search/jql?jql=assignee=currentUser()&maxResults=160&fields=id,key,summary,description,created,updated,duedate,resolutiondate,assignee,reporter,issuetype,comment,status
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Basic {{base64-encoded-username:token}}

### Get Specific Issue
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/rest/api/2/issue/TEST-1
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Basic {{base64-encoded-username:token}}

### Get Issue with Specific Fields
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/rest/api/2/issue/TEST-1?fields=summary,description,status
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Basic {{base64-encoded-username:token}}

### Get Issue Transitions
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/rest/api/2/issue/TEST-1/transitions
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Basic {{base64-encoded-username:token}}

### Transition Issue (Example: Move to In Progress)
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/rest/api/2/issue/TEST-1/transitions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Basic {{base64-encoded-username:token}}

{
  "transition": {
    "id": "21"
  }
}

### Update Issue
PUT http://127.0.0.1:8000/rest/api/2/issue/TEST-1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Basic {{base64-encoded-username:token}}

{
  "fields": {
    "summary": "Updated issue summary"
  }
}

### Create New Issue
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/rest/api/2/issue
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Basic {{base64-encoded-username:token}}

{
  "fields": {
    "project": {
      "key": "TEST"
    },
    "summary": "New issue created via API",
    "description": "This is a test issue created through the proxy",
    "issuetype": {
      "name": "Task"
    }
  }
}

### Get All Projects
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/rest/api/2/project
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Basic {{base64-encoded-username:token}}

### Get Specific Project
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/rest/api/2/project/TEST
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Basic {{base64-encoded-username:token}}

### Example with Bearer Token Authentication
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/rest/api/2/serverInfo
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{your-api-token}}

